cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with parsing animals using synthetic images and ground truth generated from CAD animal models. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel consistency-constrained semi-supervised learning method to bootstrap weak models trained on synthetic data with unlabeled real images. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses synthetic data to improve the performance of models on real images, which is a common application of AI. 
4. cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible category as the paper uses CAD animal models to generate synthetic images and ground truth. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) is also a possible category as the paper deals with parsing highly deformable animals, which is relevant to robotics applications such as animal-inspired robots.
